h non-deployment stance.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Share research governance and ethics frameworks (consent, risk disclosure) to adapt best practices across sensitive domains.\", \"Co-design user-research and usability testing methodologies for vulnerable participant groups applicable to both pilots.\", \"Cross-publish findings about human factors and trust to inform policymakers on adoption thresholds for technology in public contexts.\"]}, {\"title\": \"CareLink Home: Coordinated Support for Elderly People Living Independently\", \"match\": 30, \"similarities\": \"Both prioritize dignity, consent, human-in-the-loop decision models, and careful, non-intrusive piloting with institutional partners and ethical oversight.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain and technology: CareLink Home focuses on assisted-living sensors and care coordination; TrustVote Lab focuses on secure voting systems and cryptographic/audit tech.\", \"Customer segments: CareLink is B2G/B2B for municipalities and service providers; TrustVote Lab is research partnerships and academic institutions.\", \"Operational risk profile: CareLink involves ongoing operational monitoring; TrustVote Lab restricts pilots to non-binding, experimental contexts to avoid electoral risk.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Exchange human-centred pilot governance models for consent and data minimization in field pilots.\", \"Run joint workshops on accessibility and inclusion practices relevant to vulnerable populations in digital systems.\", \"Share audit and logging infrastructure approaches for transparent incident analysis across socially?sensitive pilots.\"]}, {\"title\": \"MoveWell Rehab: Personalized Physical Rehabilitation for Chronic Conditions\", \"match\": 28, \"similarities\": \"Both are evidence-first, research-aligned digital health/tech initiatives emphasizing professional oversight, ethical limits (not replacing core institutions), and pilot-based evaluation.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: MoveWell is clinical/rehabili