ion of non-binding pilot results.\"]}, {\"title\": \"LocalHands: Community-Based Support for Informal Caregivers\", \"match\": 35, \"similarities\": \"Both projects prioritize community trust, participatory/co-designed governance, and non-profit or public-oriented funding models with strong ethical framing.\", \"differences\": [\"Service model: LocalHands is a community platform for peer support; TrustVote Lab is a research lab conducting technical pilots.\", \"Operational cadence: LocalHands centers ongoing community facilitation; TrustVote Lab runs time-limited experimental pilots with technical audits.\", \"Primary stakeholders: LocalHands focuses on caregivers and municipalities; TrustVote Lab focuses on researchers, auditors, and electoral stakeholders.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Exchange approaches to community trust-building and participatory governance for sensitive public-interest pilots.\", \"Pilot joint community workshops to surface citizen concerns about technology and democratic processes.\", \"Co-produce public communication templates that explain experimental findings in non-technical, trust-building language.\"]}, {\"title\": \"AccessPath: Inclusive Employment Pathways for People with Disabilities\", \"match\": 30, \"similarities\": \"Both center inclusion, co-design with affected communities, ethical governance, and careful non-exploitative implementation practices.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: AccessPath focuses on employment and workplace accommodations; TrustVote Lab focuses on voting technology research and democratic legitimacy.\", \"User involvement: AccessPath empowers job seekers in role design; TrustVote Lab involves participants in non-binding pilots and audit processes.\", \"Scale and monetization: AccessPath has B2B/B2G service contracts; TrustVote Lab is research-funded with limited commercialization.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Collaborate on accessibility standards and testing protocols for digital interfaces used in civic tech pilots