riorities: StageNext emphasizes streaming and rights management; TrustVote Lab emphasizes security audits and cryptographic verifiability.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Share best practices for designing non-binding pilot environments that protect participant rights and creative control.\", \"Co-host public dissemination events that use accessible narratives to explain technical pilot findings to broader cultural audiences.\", \"Develop guidelines to translate technical audit results into clear public communications suited for non-technical stakeholders.\"]}, {\"title\": \"Memory Trails: Cultural Routes for Territorial Memory and Education\", \"match\": 40, \"similarities\": \"Both prioritize ethical community engagement, public education, responsible public-facing documentation, and pilot projects developed with local institutions and scholars.\", \"differences\": [\"Subject matter: Memory Trails focuses on place-based historical narratives; TrustVote Lab focuses on technical evaluation of voting systems.\", \"Delivery: Memory Trails blends physical signage with digital layers; TrustVote Lab runs technical pilot deployments and security audits.\", \"Primary outcomes: Memory Trails produces educational routes and cultural resources; TrustVote Lab produces audit reports and technical evidence for policy.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Coordinate on community co-creation methods and ethical framing for public-facing documentation of pilots.\", \"Share tools for contextualizing technical findings within local civic narratives to improve public understanding.\", \"Pilot mixed-format public engagement (walking tours + public research presentations) to translate technical risk into lived civic contexts.\"]}, {\"title\": \"OpenCouncil: Transparent Decision Tracking for Local Governments\", \"match\": 75, \"similarities\": \"Strong alignment on improving democratic trust, transparency, institutional integration with public administrations, citizen-facing clarity, and B2G partnership