65, \"similarities\": \"Strong overlap in community-driven design, municipal partnerships, peer networks, facilitation-led models, and aims to strengthen local social resilience and reduce pressure on formal services.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain focus: LocalHands explicitly targets informal caregivers and peer support; NeighbourLab targets broader neighborhood social challenges and participatory resource allocation.\", \"Service model: LocalHands centers mutual aid networks and caregiver recognition; NeighbourLab centers deliberation, budgeting, and institutional facilitation.\", \"Operational tools: LocalHands emphasizes resource libraries and community coordination; NeighbourLab emphasizes participatory budgeting, transparent decision flows, and platform governance.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Integrate LocalHands community networks into NeighbourLab pilots to co-design caregiver support projects and budgets.\", \"Share facilitator training and moderation best practices to support sustained local engagement.\", \"Joint measurement of social impact (reduced isolation, continuity of services) and co-funding opportunities with municipalities.\"]}, {\"title\": \"AccessPath: Inclusive Employment Pathways for People with Disabilities\", \"match\": 40, \"similarities\": \"Both prioritize co-design, person/community-centered processes, institutional partnerships (employers or municipalities), and sustained advisory/implementation support to achieve social inclusion outcomes.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: AccessPath targets employment inclusion for people with disabilities and co-designed job roles; NeighbourLab targets neighborhood governance and community-led initiatives.\", \"Primary beneficiaries: AccessPath’s primary users are job seekers with disabilities and employers; NeighbourLab’s are neighborhood residents and civic actors.\", \"Core functionality: AccessPath provides profile-based co-design tools and onboarding guidance; NeighbourLab provides participatory budgeting, deliberation, and governance tooling.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Use NeighbourLab to engage neighborhoods in identifying local employment opportunities and co-designing supported roles.\", \"Share co-design methodologies to ensure inclusive participation and accessibility of NeighbourLab tools.\", \"Pilot joint programs where participatory budgets finance supported employment initiatives designed via AccessPath.\"]}, {\"title\": \"ReLoop Materials: Circular Packaging for Local Food Producers\", \"match\": 15, \"similarities\": \"Both engage local actors (SMEs or residents) and municipal or local network partners and emphasize measurable environmental/social outcomes and integration with existing local workflows.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: ReLoop focuses on circular packaging logistics and physical container lifecycle; NeighbourLab focuses on civic participation, deliberation, and budgeting.\", \"Operational model: ReLoop requires logistics, cleaning infrastructure, and capital investment in containers; NeighbourLab is software + facilitation-oriented.\", \"Primary customers: ReLoop targets SMEs and producers; NeighbourLab targets municipal governments and neighborhood groups.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Use NeighbourLab to run community deliberations on local waste-reduction priorities and pilot funding via participatory budgeting.\", \"Coordinate with local food networks engaged by ReLoop to test neighborhood-level reuse schemes informed by resident input.\", \"Share community outreach strategies to onboard local producers and residents into circular initiatives.\"]}, {\"title\": \"EnergySense Communities: Collective Energy Efficiency for Apartment Buildings\", \"match\": 70, \"similarities\": \"Strong overlap in neighborhood-level engagement, municipal and housing-cooperative partnerships, privacy-first community data practices, collective challenges and behavior-change techniques, and B2G/B2B institutional sales models.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: EnergySense targets building-level energy efficiency using aggregated smart-meter data; NeighbourLab targets broader social challenges and decision power via participatory budgeting.\", \"Data needs: EnergySense relies on smart meter integrations and anonymized energy analytics; NeighbourLab focuses on participatory processes and resource allocation data.\", \"Primary outputs: EnergySense outputs verified energy reductions and collective goals; NeighbourLab outputs locally owned initiatives and funded projects.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Pilot integrated programs where NeighbourLab facilitates neighborhood decision-making about energy retrofits and allocates participatory budgets toward agreed measures.\", \"Share engagement mechanics for community challenges and resident committees to sustain behavior change.\", \"Combine anonymized energy insights with participatory deliberation to co-create low-cost, high-impact building actions.\"]}, {\"title\": \"SoilBack: Regenerative Practices for Small-Scale Agriculture\", \"match\": 20, \"similarities\": \"Both promote peer learning, localized, practice-first approaches, and partnerships with local organizations (cooperatives or neighborhood groups) and value transparent, non-financialized impact indicators.\", \"differences\": [\"Domain: SoilBack serves small-scale farmers and agronomic practice change; NeighbourLab serves urban neighborhoods and civic decision-making.\", \"Technology and operations: SoilBack relies on agronomic advisory, field indicators and regional adaptation; NeighbourLab relies on digital deliberation and budgeting tools.\", \"Revenue/customers: SoilBack is subscription and cooperative-focused for farmers; NeighbourLab is B2G municipal licensing for participatory programs.\"], \"collaboration\": [\"Use NeighbourLab’s participatory frameworks to co-design rural/regional community regeneration initiatives and allocate funds to pilot regenerative practices.\", \"Share peer-learning methods and community moni